population.description: Target population defined by eligibility criteria

objectives.name: Primary Efficacy Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy of upadacitinib compared to placebo in subjects with active psoriatic arthritis (PsA) who have had an inadequate response or intolerance to at least 1 bDMARD

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objectives
objectives.text: To evaluate key secondary efficacy endpoints of upadacitinib versus placebo

objectives.name: Safety Objective
objectives.text: Safety evaluations include adverse event (AE) monitoring, physical examinations, vital sign measurements, electrocardiogram (ECG), and clinical laboratory testing (hematology, chemistry, and urinalysis) as a measure of safety and tolerability for the entire study duration.

objectives.name: Pharmacokinetic Objective
objectives.text: Blood samples for assay of upadacitinib and possibly other medications in plasma will be collected at each visit after baseline in Period 1.

objectives.name: Exploratory Research Objective
objectives.text: Prognostic, surrogate, predictive, and pharmacodynamic biomarkers signatures may be evaluated.

endpoints.name: Primary Efficacy Endpoint
endpoints.text: proportion of subjects achieving ACR20 response at Week 12

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 1
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in HAQ-DI at Week 12

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 2
endpoints.text: Static Investigator Global Assessment (sIGA) of Psoriasis of 0 or 1 and at least a 2-point improvement from baseline at Week 16

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 3
endpoints.text: Psoriasis Area Severity Index (PASI) 75 response at Week 16 (for subjects with  3% BSA psoriasis at baseline)

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 4
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in SF-36 PCS at Week 12

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 5
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in FACIT-Fatigue Questionnaire at Week 12

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 6
endpoints.text: Proportion of subjects achieving Minimal Disease Activity (MDA) at Week 24

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 7
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in Self-Assessment of Psoriasis Symptoms (SAPS) Questionnaire at Week 16

endpoints.name: Safety Endpoints
endpoints.text: AEs, physical examination, laboratory assessments, ECG, and vital signs

endpoints.name: Pharmacokinetic Endpoints
endpoints.text: population central values and the empirical Bayesian estimates of the individual values of upadacitinib oral clearance (CL/F) and volume of distribution (V/F)

endpoints.name: Exploratory Endpoints
endpoints.text: nucleic acids, proteins, metabolites, or lipids

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Age requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Adult male or female, at least  18 years old at Screening.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: PsA Diagnosis and CASPAR
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Clinical diagnosis of PsA with symptom onset at least 6 months prior to the Screening Visit and fulfillment of the Classification Criteria for PsA (CASPAR).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Active Disease at Baseline
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject has active disease at Baseline defined as  3 tender joints (based on 68 joint counts) and  3 swollen joints (based on 66 joint counts) at Screening and Baseline Visits.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Plaque Psoriasis History
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Diagnosis of active plaque psoriasis or documented history of plaque psoriasis.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: bDMARD Inadequate Response
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject has had an inadequate response (lack of efficacy after a minimum 12 week duration of therapy) or intolerance to treatment with at least 1 bDMARD.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: bDMARD Discontinuation
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subjects must have discontinued all bDMARDs prior to the first dose of study drug. Subjects who need to discontinue bDMARDs prior to the Baseline Visit to comply with this inclusion criterion must follow the procedure specified below or at least five times the mean terminal elimination half-life of a drug:  4 weeks for etanercept;  8 weeks for adalimumab, infliximab, certolizumab, golimumab, abatacept, tocilizumab, and ixekizumab;  16 weeks for secukinumab;  12 weeks for ustekinumab;  1 year for rituximab OR  6 months if B cells have returned to pretreatment level or normal reference range (local lab) if pretreatment levels are not available.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Concomitant non-biologic DMARDs
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject who is on current treatment with concomitant non-biologic DMARDs at study entry must be on  2 non-biologic DMARDs (except the combination of MTX and leflunomide) at the following doses: MTX ( 25 mg/week), SSZ (3000 mg/day), leflunomide (LEF) (20 mg/day), apremilast (60 mg/day), HCQ ( 400 mg/day), bucillamine (300 mg/day) and iguratimod (50 mg/day) for  12 weeks and at stable dose for 4 weeks prior to the Baseline Visit. No other DMARDs are permitted during the study.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Stable NSAIDs/Corticosteroids
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Stable doses of NSAIDs, acetaminophen/paracetamol, low-potency opiates (tramadol or combination of acetaminophen and codeine or hydrocodone), oral corticosteroids (equivalent to prednisone  10 mg/day), or inhaled corticosteroids for stable medical conditions are allowed, but must have been at a stable dose for 1 weeks prior to the Baseline Visit.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Opiate and TCM Discontinuation
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subjects must have discontinued all opiates (except for tramadol or combination of acetaminophen and codeine or hydrocodone) at least 1 week and oral Traditional Chinese Medicine for at least 4 weeks prior to the first dose of study drug.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Pregnancy Test
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Women of childbearing potential, must not have a positive serum pregnancy test at the Screening Visit and must have a negative urine pregnancy test at the Baseline Visit prior to study drug dosing.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Contraception Requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: If female, subject must be postmenopausal OR permanently surgically sterile OR for Women of Childbearing Potential practicing at least one protocol specified method of birth control, that is effective from the Baseline visit through at least 30 days after the last dose of study drug.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Informed Consent
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subjects must voluntarily sign and date an informed consent, approved by an Independent Ethics Committee (IEC)/Institutional Review Board (IRB), prior to the initiation of any screening or study-specific procedures.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: JAK Inhibitor Exposure
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Prior exposure to any Janus Kinase (JAK) inhibitor (including but not limited to ruxolitinib, tofacitinib, baricitinib, and filgotinib).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Excessive DMARDs
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Current treatment with > 2 non-biologic DMARDs or use of DMARDs other than MTX, SSZ, LEF, apremilast, HCQ, bucillamine or iguratimod or use of MTX in combination with LEF at Baseline.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Investigational Drug Use
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Has been treated with any investigational drug within 30 days or five half-lives of the drug (whichever is longer) prior to the first dose of study drug or is currently enrolled in another interventional clinical study.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Infection History
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Current or past history of infection including: History of recurrent or disseminated (even a single episode) herpes zoster; History of disseminated (even a single episode) herpes simplex; History of known invasive infection (e.g., listeriosis and histoplasmosis); Active human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) or immunodeficiency syndrome; Subject has active TB or meets TB exclusionary parameters; Active infection(s) requiring treatment with parenteral anti-infectives within 30 days, or oral anti-infectives within 14 days prior to the Baseline Visit; Chronic recurring infection and/or active viral infection; Active HBV or HCV.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Underlying Medical Diseases
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Underlying medical diseases or problems including but not limited to: History of cardiovascular conditions (recent CVA, MI, stenting, uncontrolled hypertension); Organ transplant recipient; History of gastrointestinal perforation, diverticulitis; Conditions interfering with drug absorption; History of malignancy except NMSC or CIS of cervix; Clinically significant medical conditions; Wheelchair-bound or bedridden.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Psoriasis Treatments
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Use of concomitant psoriasis treatments within specified timeframe: Phototherapy (4 weeks), Laser therapy (4 weeks), Topical psoriasis treatments (2 weeks).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Other Inflammatory Diseases
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of fibromyalgia, any arthritis with onset prior to age 17 years, or current diagnosis of inflammatory joint disease other than PsA (including, but not limited to rheumatoid arthritis, gout, overlap connective tissue diseases, scleroderma, polymyositis, dermatomyositis, systemic lupus erythematosus).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Drug or Alcohol Abuse
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of clinically significant (per Investigator's judgment) drug or alcohol abuse within the last 6 months preceding the Baseline Visit.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Pregnancy and Breastfeeding
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Female subject who is pregnant, breastfeeding or is considering becoming pregnant during the study or within 30 days after the last dose of study drug.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Laboratory Values
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Laboratory values meeting the following criteria within the Screening period: AST/ALT > 2 x ULN; GFR < 40 mL/min/1.73m2; WBC < 2,500/L; ANC < 1,500/L; Platelet count < 100,000/L; ALC < 800/L; Hemoglobin < 10 g/dL.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Other Skin Disease
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Active skin disease other than psoriasis that would interfere with the assessment of psoriasis.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Extra-articular Manifestations
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject with extra-articular manifestations of PsA (e.g., PsO, uveitis, or IBD) that are not clinically stable for at least 30 days prior to study entry.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Joint Surgery or Injections
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject has had joint surgery at joints to be assessed within this study or has been treated with intra-articular, intramuscular, intravenous, trigger point or tender point, intra-bursa, or intra-tendon sheath corticosteroids in the preceding 8 weeks prior to the Baseline visit.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Investigator Discretion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Consideration by the Investigator, for any reason, that the subject is an unsuitable candidate to receive upadacitinib.
